<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Unfortunately Geiger has not indulged on the specific limitations. NT</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:14 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Unfortunately Geiger has not indulged on the specific limitations. NT<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=753" TARGET=_self>There are lots of solutions, Q is what will Verant do for us?</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I think you should approach Verant and ask them what the are and

<BR>&gt; are not willing to do to support the PvP community. There are a
<BR>&gt; lot ofchanges and improvements that can be added to make PvP a
<BR>&gt; workable system in Everquest, the real question is what can Brad
<BR>&gt; and the dev team do for us in the near future? I understand they
<BR>&gt; are very busy with bug fixes and getting the game out the door.
<BR>&gt; Be that as it may, will the PvP community have a chance? Will
<BR>&gt; Verant help us by changing some of the algorithms for PVP
<BR>&gt; specific combat?
<P>&gt; Once we know what limitations we are working under we can better
<BR>&gt; address possible solutions. If the worse case scenario is true,
<BR>&gt; and no additional changes or support are intended for PvP in
<BR>&gt; everquest, then by all means let us know now so we can go to the
<BR>&gt; -PvP servers and try to enjoy that aspect of the game, rather
<BR>&gt; than waste further time and effort on these discussions.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
